# Child Process

The `child_process` module is how Node.js runs external programs. Choose the right method based on your needs: `exec` for simple commands, `execFile` for safe direct execution, `spawn` for streaming, and `fork` for Node-to-Node IPC.

## exec — Simple Shell Commands

```javascript
import { exec } from 'node:child_process';
import { promisify } from 'node:util';

const execAsync = promisify(exec);

// Run a shell command and capture buffered output
const { stdout, stderr } = await execAsync('git status --short');
console.log(stdout);

// Set working directory, timeout, and buffer size
const { stdout: files } = await execAsync('ls -la', {
  cwd: '/tmp',
  timeout: 5000,
  maxBuffer: 10 * 1024 * 1024, // 10MB (default is 1MB)
});

// Shell features work: pipes, globbing, redirection
const { stdout: count } = await execAsync('find . -name "*.js" | wc -l');
```

```javascript
// execSync — blocks the event loop, use only in CLI scripts
import { execSync } from 'node:child_process';
const version = execSync('node --version', { encoding: 'utf-8' }).trim();
```

## execFile — Safer Direct Execution

```javascript
import { execFile } from 'node:child_process';
import { promisify } from 'node:util';

const execFileAsync = promisify(execFile);

// No shell — arguments passed directly to binary, preventing injection
const { stdout } = await execFileAsync('git', ['log', '--oneline', '-5']);
const { stdout: nodeVer } = await execFileAsync('node', ['--version']);

// Preferred when you have a known binary + arguments
// User input is safe because no shell interprets metacharacters
const { stdout: result } = await execFileAsync('./my-tool', ['--input', userFile]);
```

## spawn — Streaming for Long-Running Processes

```javascript
import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';

// Inherit all stdio — preserves terminal colors and interactivity
const build = spawn('npm', ['run', 'build'], {
  cwd: '/path/to/project',
  stdio: 'inherit',
});
build.on('close', (code) => console.log(`Build exited: ${code}`));

// Capture output as streams
const proc = spawn('git', ['log', '--oneline', '-20']);
let output = '';
proc.stdout.on('data', (chunk) => { output += chunk; });
proc.stderr.on('data', (chunk) => { process.stderr.write(chunk); });
proc.on('close', (code) => {
  if (code === 0) console.log(output);
  else console.error(`Failed with code ${code}`);
});

// Pipe between processes (like shell pipes)
const grep = spawn('grep', ['error']);
const cat = spawn('cat', ['server.log']);
cat.stdout.pipe(grep.stdin);
grep.stdout.pipe(process.stdout);

// AbortController for timeout/cancellation
const controller = new AbortController();
const child = spawn('long-task', [], { signal: controller.signal });
setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), 30000);
```

## fork — Node.js IPC Workers

```javascript
import { fork } from 'node:child_process';

// Fork a Node.js module with built-in IPC channel
const worker = fork('./worker.mjs');

// Send structured messages to child
worker.send({ task: 'process', data: items });

// Receive messages from child
worker.on('message', (result) => {
  console.log('Worker result:', result);
});

worker.on('exit', (code) => {
  console.log(`Worker exited: ${code}`);
});

// In worker.mjs:
// process.on('message', (msg) => {
//   const result = doWork(msg.data);
//   process.send(result);
// });
```

## stdio Configuration

```javascript
import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';

// stdio is an array of [stdin, stdout, stderr] or a shorthand string
spawn('cmd', [], { stdio: 'inherit' });                    // forward all to parent
spawn('cmd', [], { stdio: 'pipe' });                       // all piped (default)
spawn('cmd', [], { stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe'] });   // ignore stdin, pipe out/err
spawn('cmd', [], { stdio: ['pipe', 'inherit', 'inherit'] });// pipe stdin, forward out/err
spawn('cmd', [], { stdio: 'ignore' });                     // discard all I/O

// Write to child stdin
const child = spawn('cat', [], { stdio: ['pipe', 'inherit', 'inherit'] });
child.stdin.write('hello from parent\n');
child.stdin.end();
```

## Error Handling and Exit Codes

```javascript
import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';

const child = spawn('some-tool', ['--flag']);

// ENOENT — binary not found in PATH
child.on('error', (err) => {
  if (err.code === 'ENOENT') {
    console.error('Binary not found. Is it installed and in PATH?');
  } else if (err.code === 'EACCES') {
    console.error('Permission denied. Check file permissions.');
  } else {
    console.error('Spawn error:', err.message);
  }
});

// Exit codes (0 = success) and signals (SIGTERM, SIGKILL)
child.on('close', (code, signal) => {
  if (signal) {
    console.error(`Killed by signal: ${signal}`);
  } else if (code !== 0) {
    console.error(`Exited with code: ${code}`);
  }
});
```

## Signal Handling

```javascript
import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';

const child = spawn('long-running-server', []);

// Graceful shutdown: SIGTERM first, then SIGKILL after timeout
function shutdown() {
  child.kill('SIGTERM');
  setTimeout(() => {
    if (!child.killed) {
      child.kill('SIGKILL');
    }
  }, 5000);
}

process.on('SIGINT', shutdown);
process.on('SIGTERM', shutdown);
```

## Environment Variable Passing

```javascript
import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';

// Child inherits parent env by default. Override selectively:
const child = spawn('my-tool', [], {
  env: {
    ...process.env,           // inherit everything
    NODE_ENV: 'production',   // override specific vars
    API_KEY: 'secret',        // add new vars
  },
});

// Minimal env (only what the child needs)
const minimal = spawn('my-tool', [], {
  env: {
    PATH: process.env.PATH,
    HOME: process.env.HOME,
    MY_CONFIG: 'value',
  },
});
```

## Cross-Platform Considerations

```javascript
import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';

// On Windows, use { shell: true } to run .cmd and .bat files
const child = spawn('npm', ['run', 'build'], {
  shell: process.platform === 'win32',
});

// Or use cross-spawn package for consistent behavior
// import spawn from 'cross-spawn';
// const child = spawn('npm', ['run', 'build']);
```

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `PATH` | Directories searched for executables when spawning commands |
| `SHELL` | Default shell used by `exec` on Unix (`/bin/sh` if unset) |
| `COMSPEC` | Default shell used by `exec` on Windows (`cmd.exe` if unset) |
| `NODE_OPTIONS` | Options passed to forked Node.js child processes |
| `NODE_PATH` | Additional module search paths inherited by forked children |
